<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-104-069  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 104 069.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  June 18 1990 n305 p41(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CoCom eases export rules; an array of restrictions are lifted.andO;(Coordinating Committee on Multilateral Export Controls)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Schenker, Jennifer L.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The 17-nation Coordinating Committee on Multilateral ExportControls eases restrictions on the export of an array ofcommunications equipment to Eastern European nations.andP;  Among thetechnologies are Gateways and some types of LAN products, whichwill now be in the favorable consideration category.andP;  In addition,controls on analog mobile radio equipment will be reduced, as willcontrol on packet switches with a maximum port throughput of9,600-bps.andP;  Under the more liberal regulations, East Germany willbe able to import all types of telecommunications equipment andCzechoslovakia, Hungary and Poland will be allowed to import fiberoptic transmission equipment.andP;  The Soviet Union will still be offlimits for fiber optic equipment with speeds of 45M-bps or higher.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Coordination Committee for Multilateral Export ControlsExportTechnology TransferCommunications EquipmentGovernment RegulationEurope.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>